What is the remainder when $129^{34}+96^{38}$ is divided by $11$?
inference:
To find the remainder when $129^{34}+96^{38}$ is divided by $11$, we first find the remainders when each term is divided by $11$.
$129 = 11 \times 11 + 8$, so $129 \equiv 8 \pmod{11}$.
Then $129^{34} \equiv 8^{34} \pmod{11}$.
$8^1 \equiv 8 \pmod{11}$
$8^2 \equiv 64 \equiv 9 \pmod{11}$
$8^3 \equiv 8^2 \times 8 \equiv 9 \times 8 \equiv 72 \equiv 72 - 66 \equiv 6 \pmod{11}$
$8^4 \equiv 8^3 \times 8 \equiv 6 \times 8 \equiv 48 \equiv 48 - 44 \equiv 4 \pmod{11}$
$8^5 \equiv 8^4 \times 8 \equiv 4 \times 8 \equiv 32 \equiv 32 - 22 \equiv 10 \pmod{11}$
$8^6 \equiv 8^5 \times 8 \equiv 10 \times 8 \equiv 80 \equiv 80 - 77 \equiv 3 \pmod{11}$
$8^7 \equiv 8^6 \times 8 \equiv 3 \times 8 \equiv 24 \equiv 24 - 22 \equiv 2 \pmod{11}$
$8^8 \equiv 8^7 \times 8 \equiv 2 \times 8 \equiv 16 \equiv 16 - 11 \equiv 5 \pmod{11}$
$8^9 \equiv 8^8 \times 8 \equiv 5 \times 8 \equiv 40 \equiv 40 - 33 \equiv 7 \pmod{11}$
$8^{10} \equiv 8^9 \times 8 \equiv 7 \times 8 \equiv 56 \equiv 56 - 44 \equiv 12 \equiv 1 \pmod{11}$
Since $8^{10} \equiv 1 \pmod{11}$, $8^{34} = 8^{10 \times 3 + 4} = (8^{10})^3 \times 8^4 \equiv 1^3 \times 8^4 \equiv 1 \times 4 \equiv 4 \pmod{11}$.

$96 = 11 \times 8 + 8$, so $96 \equiv 8 \pmod{11}$.
Then $96^{38} \equiv 8^{38} = (8^{10})^3 \times 8^8 \equiv 1^3 \times 8^8 \equiv 1 \times 5 \equiv 5 \pmod{11}$.

Therefore, $129^{34}+96^{38} \equiv 4+5 \equiv 9 \pmod{11}$.

Final Answer: $\boxed{9}$ I hope it is correct.
ground_truth:
We use the property that $a \equiv b \pmod{m}$ implies $a^c \equiv b^c \pmod{m}$.

Since $129 \equiv -3 \pmod{11}$ and $96 \equiv -3 \pmod{11}$, we have  $$129^{34}+96^{38} \equiv (-3)^{34}+(-3)^{38} \equiv 3^{34}+3^{38} \pmod{11}.$$Since $3^5 \equiv 1 \pmod{11},$ we can see that $3^{34} = (3^5)^{6} \cdot 3^4$ and $3^{38} = (3^5)^{7} \cdot 3^3.$

Then,  \begin{align*}
129^{34}+96^{38}&\equiv (3^5)^{6} \cdot 3^4 + (3^5)^{7} \cdot 3^3\\
& \equiv 3^4 + 3^3\\
& \equiv 81 + 27\\
& \equiv 108 \\
&\equiv \boxed{9} \pmod{11}.
\end{align*}
